channel.title: Working Ubuntu Webclients[Project]
channel.description:
Note: I am Loveandpower, my account is hacked or something will an admin or somebody look at it please :S
Anywho, here is a quick tutorial on how to get it working. I tested this on deathchaos9 webclient. (for proof ask him if he has a "loveandpower" in his character files :P )
You need to install the following programs
-Wine -Winetricks -The third program is below
This next step really depends on your version of ubuntu, on 11.04 it was unneeded not sure about the other versions.
Type in this command to a terminal:
sh winetricks vcrun6 wsh56
Now download this dll file and add it to your wine system32 folder. (.wine/windows/system32/)
http://www.dll-files.com/dllindex/dll-files.shtml?msvbvm60
Next step is to download java here THROUGH Wine http://www.java.com/en/download/manual.jsp , make sure you download the OFFLINE one.
Known bugs:
-Sprites may be partially messed up but that would be a client issue.
~~Post any other bugs you find so I can help improve this~~

item.title: Working Ubuntu Webclients[Project]
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“Moparisthebest, post:13, topic:412630”][quote author=zyle1992 link=topic=514109.msg3746792#msg3746792 date=1315762369]

I was referring to how some clients load files without caring about case sensitivity. For example, the file name would be “HEADICONS_1.PNG” and the client would load it as “HEADICONS_1.png”. See the problem there?

No because the extensions in any operating system are not case sensitive. Only the name.

file.png == file.PNG
File.PNG != FILE.PNG
[/quote]

Where did you get that info? It’s entirely not true. A case-sensitive file system is case-sensitive everywhere, it doesn’t make exceptions for extensions, in fact it doesn’t even know what an extension is, it’s just part of a name.[/quote]

Really? Then something must be off somewhere in my Ubuntu install because file.png == file.PNG. If I save file.png, then create a new file, file.PNG it says that there is an existing file with that name, and asks if I want to replace it.

Read full topic

item.title: Working Ubuntu Webclients[Project]
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“Eddie Crosswall, post:5, topic:412630”][quote author=zyle1992 link=topic=514109.msg3731227#msg3731227 date=1314644406]
Why the hell would you use wine when Java is platform-independent?
[/quote]because the java it gives for download in the software section is not the correct java to run inside of web browsers. There are three ones, web start java, icedtea java, and some other one. You have to manually go into either your terminal or download it directly from the java site as the one that actually loads webclients is sun java. Why it has to be like this? idk lol[/quote]

sudo apt-get install openjdk-6-jdk

You now have native java libraries. If the applet doesn’t load correctly, install the missing plugins (it will give you a prompt to do so). If it still doesn’t work after that, then it’s a problem with the client (ie. cache directory being set to “C:.cache_name_here”)
